### (1) Translation  
Wei Wu Hou (Marquis Wu of Wei) planned affairs correctly, and none of his ministers could match him. After court, he had a joyful expression. Wu Qi (Wu Qi) advanced and said: "Have you ever heard the words of King Zhuang of Chu from those around you?"  
The marquis said: "What were King Zhuang of Chu's words?"  
Wu Qi replied: "King Zhuang of Chu planned affairs correctly, and none of his ministers could match him. After court, he had a worried expression. Shen Gong Wuchen (Shen Gong Wuchen) inquired: 'The king has a worried expression after court—why is that?'  
The king said: 'This unworthy one plans affairs correctly, and none of my ministers can match me—therefore I am worried. It is as the words of Zhongkui say: "When feudal lords find a teacher for themselves, they become kings; when they find a friend, they become hegemons; when they find only doubters, they survive; when they rely solely on their own planning and have no one who can surpass them, they perish." Now, with my lack of worthiness, yet none of my ministers can match me—my state is nearly perished! Therefore I am worried.'  
King Zhuang was worried, while you, my lord, are joyful."  
The marquis hesitated, bowed twice, and said: "Heaven has sent you, Master, to correct my fault."

